  <!-- 1. OVERVIEW -->
  <div class="section" id="overview">
    <div class="section-label"><span class="section-num">1</span>Project overview</div>
    <h2>What you're building</h2>
    <p>A production-ready <strong>Task Manager application</strong> — a real app companies actually build. It has a React frontend, Node.js REST API, PostgreSQL database, Redis for session caching, and Nginx as a reverse proxy. Every service runs in its own container with proper networking, volumes, health checks, and monitoring.</p>

    <div class="grid3" style="margin-top:20px;">
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-icon">🎯</div>
        <h4>What this covers</h4>
        <p>Multi-stage builds, named volumes, custom networks, health checks, depends_on, environment variables, secrets, Nginx proxy, monitoring stack.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-icon">💼</div>
