  <!-- 4. DOCKERFILES -->
  <div class="section" id="dockerfiles">
    <div class="section-label"><span class="section-num">4</span>Dockerfiles</div>
    <h2>Multi-stage Dockerfiles <span class="interview-badge">🎯 Most asked</span></h2>

    <h3>Backend — Node.js API</h3>
    <div class="code-wrap">
      <div class="code-title"><span class="filename">backend/Dockerfile</span><span>Multi-stage production build</span></div>
      <pre><span class="c"># ═══════════════════════════════</span>
<span class="c"># Stage 1: Install dependencies</span>
<span class="c"># ═══════════════════════════════</span>
<span class="k">FROM</span> <span class="v">node:18-alpine</span> <span class="k">AS</span> <span class="s">deps</span>
<span class="k">WORKDIR</span> <span class="s">/app</span>

<span class="c"># Copy only package files first (layer cache trick)</span>
<span class="k">COPY</span> package*.json ./
<span class="k">RUN</span> npm ci --only=production && npm cache clean --force

<span class="c"># ═══════════════════════════════</span>
<span class="c"># Stage 2: Production image</span>
<span class="c"># ═══════════════════════════════</span>
<span class="k">FROM</span> <span class="v">node:18-alpine</span> <span class="k">AS</span> <span class="s">production</span>

<span class="c"># Security: create non-root user</span>
<span class="k">RUN</span> addgroup -S appgroup && \
    adduser -S appuser -G appgroup

<span class="k">WORKDIR</span> <span class="s">/app</span>

<span class="c"># Copy deps from stage 1 (no build tools)</span>
<span class="k">COPY</span> <span class="f">--from=deps</span> /app/node_modules ./node_modules
<span class="k">COPY</span> <span class="f">--chown=appuser:appgroup</span> src/ ./src/
<span class="k">COPY</span> <span class="f">--chown=appuser:appgroup</span> package.json ./

<span class="c"># Metadata</span>
<span class="k">LABEL</span> maintainer=<span class="s">"devops-team"</span>
<span class="k">LABEL</span> version=<span class="s">"1.0"</span>
<span class="k">LABEL</span> description=<span class="s">"TaskManager API"</span>

<span class="c"># Runtime config</span>
<span class="k">ENV</span> NODE_ENV=<span class="v">production</span>
<span class="k">ENV</span> PORT=<span class="v">5000</span>
<span class="k">USER</span> appuser
<span class="k">EXPOSE</span> <span class="v">5000</span>

<span class="c"># Health check</span>
<span class="k">HEALTHCHECK</span> --interval=<span class="v">30s</span> --timeout=<span class="v">10s</span> \
  --start-period=<span class="v">15s</span> --retries=<span class="v">3</span> \
  <span class="k">CMD</span> wget <span class="f">-qO-</span> http://localhost:5000/health || exit 1

<span class="k">CMD</span> [<span class="s">"node"</span>, <span class="s">"src/app.js"</span>]</pre>
    </div>

    <h3 style="margin-top:24px;">Frontend — React App</h3>
    <div class="code-wrap">
      <div class="code-title"><span class="filename">frontend/Dockerfile</span><span>3-stage: build → test → nginx serve</span></div>
      <pre><span class="c"># Stage 1: Install deps</span>
<span class="k">FROM</span> <span class="v">node:18-alpine</span> <span class="k">AS</span> <span class="s">deps</span>
<span class="k">WORKDIR</span> <span class="s">/app</span>
<span class="k">COPY</span> package*.json ./
<span class="k">RUN</span> npm ci

<span class="c"># Stage 2: Build React app</span>
<span class="k">FROM</span> <span class="v">node:18-alpine</span> <span class="k">AS</span> <span class="s">builder</span>
<span class="k">WORKDIR</span> <span class="s">/app</span>
<span class="k">COPY</span> <span class="f">--from=deps</span> /app/node_modules ./node_modules
<span class="k">COPY</span> . .
<span class="k">ARG</span> REACT_APP_API_URL
<span class="k">ENV</span> REACT_APP_API_URL=$REACT_APP_API_URL
<span class="k">RUN</span> npm run build

<span class="c"># Stage 3: Serve with Nginx (tiny final image ~25MB)</span>
<span class="k">FROM</span> <span class="v">nginx:1.25-alpine</span> <span class="k">AS</span> <span class="s">production</span>
<span class="k">COPY</span> <span class="f">--from=builder</span> /app/build /usr/share/nginx/html
<span class="k">COPY</span> nginx.conf /etc/nginx/conf.d/default.conf
<span class="k">EXPOSE</span> <span class="v">3000</span>
<span class="k">HEALTHCHECK</span> <span class="k">CMD</span> wget <span class="f">-qO-</span> http://localhost:3000 || exit 1
<span class="k">CMD</span> [<span class="s">"nginx"</span>, <span class="s">"-g"</span>, <span class="s">"daemon off;"</span>]</pre>
    </div>

    <h3 style="margin-top:24px;">Dev Dockerfile (with hot reload)</h3>
    <div class="code-wrap">
      <div class="code-title"><span class="filename">backend/Dockerfile.dev</span><span>Development only</span></div>
      <pre><span class="k">FROM</span> <span class="v">node:18-alpine</span>
<span class="k">WORKDIR</span> <span class="s">/app</span>
<span class="k">RUN</span> npm install <span class="f">-g</span> nodemon
<span class="k">COPY</span> package*.json ./
<span class="k">RUN</span> npm install       <span class="c"># includes devDependencies</span>
<span class="k">COPY</span> . .
<span class="k">EXPOSE</span> <span class="v">5000</span>
<span class="c"># nodemon watches for file changes and restarts</span>
<span class="k">CMD</span> [<span class="s">"nodemon"</span>, <span class="s">"src/app.js"</span>]</pre>
    </div>
    <div class="callout tip">
      <span class="callout-icon">💡</span>
      <div class="callout-body"><strong>Why two Dockerfiles?</strong> Dockerfile.dev is for local development with hot-reload (nodemon) and devDependencies. Dockerfile (production) is slim, non-root, no dev tools. This is standard practice in real companies.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- 5. DOCKER COMPOSE -->
  <div class="section" id="compose">
    <div class="section-label"><span class="section-num">5</span>Docker Compose</div>
    <h2>docker-compose.yml — the core file <span class="interview-badge">🎯 Know this cold</span></h2>

    <div class="code-wrap">
      <div class="code-title"><span class="filename">docker-compose.yml</span><span>Development environment</span></div>
      <pre><span class="v">version</span>: <span class="s">'3.8'</span>

<span class="v">services</span>:

  <span class="c"># ─── Nginx Reverse Proxy ──────────────────</span>
  <span class="e">nginx</span>:
    <span class="k">build</span>: ./nginx
    <span class="k">container_name</span>: tm_nginx
    <span class="k">ports</span>:
      - <span class="s">"80:80"</span>       <span class="c"># ONLY service exposed to host</span>
    <span class="k">depends_on</span>:
      frontend:
        <span class="k">condition</span>: service_healthy
      backend:
        <span class="k">condition</span>: service_healthy
    <span class="k">networks</span>:
      - frontend_net
      - backend_net
    <span class="k">restart</span>: unless-stopped

  <span class="c"># ─── React Frontend ───────────────────────</span>
  <span class="e">frontend</span>:
    <span class="k">build</span>:
      <span class="k">context</span>: ./frontend
      <span class="k">dockerfile</span>: Dockerfile.dev
    <span class="k">container_name</span>: tm_frontend
    <span class="k">volumes</span>:
      - ./frontend/src:/app/src   <span class="c"># hot reload</span>
    <span class="k">environment</span>:
      - REACT_APP_API_URL=/api
    <span class="k">networks</span>:
      - frontend_net
    <span class="k">healthcheck</span>:
      test: [<span class="s">"CMD"</span>, <span class="s">"wget"</span>, <span class="s">"-qO-"</span>, <span class="s">"http://localhost:3000"</span>]
      interval: 30s
      timeout: 10s
      retries: 3

  <span class="c"># ─── Node.js API ──────────────────────────</span>
  <span class="e">backend</span>:
    <span class="k">build</span>:
      <span class="k">context</span>: ./backend
      <span class="k">dockerfile</span>: Dockerfile.dev
    <span class="k">container_name</span>: tm_backend
    <span class="k">volumes</span>:
      - ./backend/src:/app/src    <span class="c"># hot reload</span>
    <span class="k">environment</span>:
      - NODE_ENV=development
      - PORT=5000
      - DB_HOST=postgres
      - DB_PORT=5432
      - DB_NAME=${DB_NAME}
      - DB_USER=${DB_USER}
      - DB_PASS=${DB_PASS}
      - REDIS_URL=redis://redis:6379
    <span class="k">depends_on</span>:
      postgres:
        <span class="k">condition</span>: service_healthy
      redis:
        <span class="k">condition</span>: service_healthy
    <span class="k">networks</span>:
      - backend_net
      - db_net
    <span class="k">healthcheck</span>:
      test: [<span class="s">"CMD"</span>, <span class="s">"wget"</span>, <span class="s">"-qO-"</span>, <span class="s">"http://localhost:5000/health"</span>]
      interval: 30s
      timeout: 10s
      retries: 3
      start_period: 15s
    <span class="k">restart</span>: unless-stopped

  <span class="c"># ─── PostgreSQL Database ──────────────────</span>
  <span class="e">postgres</span>:
    <span class="k">image</span>: postgres:15-alpine
    <span class="k">container_name</span>: tm_postgres
    <span class="k">environment</span>:
      POSTGRES_DB: ${DB_NAME}
      POSTGRES_USER: ${DB_USER}
      POSTGRES_PASSWORD: ${DB_PASS}
    <span class="k">volumes</span>:
      - pgdata:/var/lib/postgresql/data   <span class="c"># persist data</span>
      - ./postgres/init.sql:/docker-entrypoint-initdb.d/init.sql
    <span class="k">networks</span>:
      - db_net
    <span class="k">healthcheck</span>:
      test: [<span class="s">"CMD-SHELL"</span>, <span class="s">"pg_isready -U ${DB_USER} -d ${DB_NAME}"</span>]
      interval: 10s
      timeout: 5s
      retries: 5
    <span class="c"># NOT exposed to host — internal only</span>

  <span class="c"># ─── Redis Cache ──────────────────────────</span>
  <span class="e">redis</span>:
    <span class="k">image</span>: redis:7-alpine
    <span class="k">container_name</span>: tm_redis
    <span class="k">command</span>: redis-server --requirepass ${REDIS_PASS}
    <span class="k">volumes</span>:
      - redisdata:/data
    <span class="k">networks</span>:
      - db_net
    <span class="k">healthcheck</span>:
      test: [<span class="s">"CMD"</span>, <span class="s">"redis-cli"</span>, <span class="s">"ping"</span>]
      interval: 10s
      timeout: 5s
      retries: 5

<span class="c"># ─── Named Volumes ────────────────────────</span>
<span class="v">volumes</span>:
  pgdata:      <span class="c"># postgres data survives container restart</span>
  redisdata:   <span class="c"># redis persistence</span>

<span class="c"># ─── Isolated Networks ────────────────────</span>
<span class="v">networks</span>:
  frontend_net:   <span class="c"># nginx ↔ frontend</span>
    driver: bridge
  backend_net:    <span class="c"># nginx ↔ backend</span>
    driver: bridge
  db_net:         <span class="c"># backend ↔ postgres ↔ redis</span>
    driver: bridge</pre>
    </div>

    <div class="callout good">
      <span class="callout-icon">✅</span>
      <div class="callout-body"><strong>Why 3 separate networks?</strong> Frontend can't directly talk to the database. Only the backend can reach the DB network. This is network segmentation — a real security pattern. Interviewers love this explanation.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- 6. NGINX -->
  <div class="section" id="nginx">
    <div class="section-label"><span class="section-num">6</span>Nginx reverse proxy</div>
    <h2>nginx.conf</h2>
    <div class="code-wrap">
      <div class="code-title"><span class="filename">nginx/nginx.conf</span><span>Routes / → frontend, /api → backend</span></div>
      <pre><span class="k">upstream</span> frontend {
  server frontend:3000;
}

<span class="k">upstream</span> backend {
  server backend:5000;
}

server {
  listen <span class="v">80</span>;
  server_name _;

  <span class="c"># Frontend — React app</span>
  location / {
    proxy_pass http://frontend;
    proxy_set_header Host $host;
    proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
  }

  <span class="c"># Backend API — proxied to Node.js</span>
  location /api/ {
    proxy_pass http://backend/;
    proxy_set_header Host $host;
    proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
    proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
  }

  <span class="c"># WebSocket support (if needed)</span>
  location /ws {
    proxy_pass http://backend;
    proxy_http_version 1.1;
    proxy_set_header Upgrade $http_upgrade;
    proxy_set_header Connection "upgrade";
  }
}</pre>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- 7. NETWORKING -->
  <div class="section" id="networking">
    <div class="section-label"><span class="section-num">7</span>Network architecture</div>
    <h2>Who can talk to who <span class="interview-badge">🎯 Security pattern</span></h2>
    <table>
      <tr><th>Service</th><th>Can reach</th><th>Cannot reach</th><th>Why</th></tr>
      <tr><td>nginx</td><td>frontend, backend</td><td class="note">postgres, redis</td><td class="note">On frontend_net + backend_net only</td></tr>
      <tr><td>frontend</td><td>nginx</td><td class="note">backend, postgres, redis</td><td class="note">On frontend_net only</td></tr>
      <tr><td>backend</td><td>postgres, redis, nginx</td><td class="note">frontend</td><td class="note">On backend_net + db_net</td></tr>
      <tr><td>postgres</td><td>backend</td><td class="note">nginx, frontend</td><td class="note">On db_net only — isolated</td></tr>
      <tr><td>redis</td><td>backend</td><td class="note">nginx, frontend</td><td class="note">On db_net only — isolated</td></tr>
    </table>
    <div class="callout warn">
      <span class="callout-icon">⚠️</span>
      <div class="callout-body"><strong>Key:</strong> Containers on different custom networks CANNOT talk to each other. Docker's built-in DNS works by container name — <code>backend</code> can ping <code>postgres</code> because both are on <code>db_net</code>.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- 8. VOLUMES -->
  <div class="section" id="volumes">
    <div class="section-label"><span class="section-num">8</span>Volume strategy</div>
    <h2>What data goes where</h2>
    <table>
      <tr><th>Volume / Mount</th><th>Type</th><th>Service</th><th>Purpose</th></tr>
      <tr><td>pgdata</td><td class="note">Named volume</td><td>postgres</td><td class="note">DB data persists across container restarts</td></tr>
      <tr><td>redisdata</td><td class="note">Named volume</td><td>redis</td><td class="note">Redis persistence (RDB snapshots)</td></tr>
      <tr><td>./backend/src:/app/src</td><td class="note">Bind mount</td><td>backend</td><td class="note">Dev hot-reload — code changes apply instantly</td></tr>
      <tr><td>./frontend/src:/app/src</td><td class="note">Bind mount</td><td>frontend</td><td class="note">Dev hot-reload for React</td></tr>
      <tr><td>init.sql → initdb.d/</td><td class="note">Bind mount</td><td>postgres</td><td class="note">Run SQL schema on first start only</td></tr>
    </table>
    <div class="callout tip">
      <span class="callout-icon">💡</span>
      <div class="callout-body"><strong>Interview answer:</strong> "In dev, I use bind mounts for source code so changes are reflected immediately. In production, I use named volumes for data and ship the built code inside the image — no bind mounts."</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- 9. ENV FILE -->
  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-label"><span class="section-num">9</span>Environment & secrets</div>
    <h2>.env file</h2>
    <div class="code-wrap">
      <div class="code-title"><span class="filename">.env</span><span>Never commit this to Git!</span></div>
