  <!-- 13. INTERVIEW Q&A -->
  <div class="section" id="interview">
    <div class="section-label"><span class="section-num">13</span>Interview Q&A from this project</div>
    <h2>Questions you can now answer from experience</h2>
    <table>
      <tr><th>Question</th><th>Your answer (from this project)</th></tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Why multi-stage build?</td>
        <td class="note">Reduced frontend image from ~1.2GB to ~25MB. Stage 1 builds with Node, Stage 2 serves static files with Nginx only.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Why separate networks?</td>
        <td class="note">Postgres and Redis are on db_net only. Frontend can't reach DB directly — network segmentation for security.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Why health checks on depends_on?</td>
        <td class="note">Without it, backend starts before postgres is ready and crashes. Health check waits for postgres to be accepting connections.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Volumes vs bind mounts?</td>
        <td class="note">Bind mounts for dev hot-reload. Named volumes for DB data in prod so data survives container recreation.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Why Redis?</td>
        <td class="note">Session caching. Avoids hitting postgres on every authenticated request. Also used for rate limiting.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Why Nginx?</td>
        <td class="note">Single port exposed (80). Routes / to React, /api to Node. SSL termination point. Load balancing if we scale.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>How did you handle secrets?</td>
        <td class="note">Via .env file (local dev). In production, Docker Secrets or vault. Never hardcoded in Dockerfile.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>How did you monitor?</td>
        <td class="note">Prometheus scrapes /metrics endpoint. Grafana dashboards for container CPU/memory/request rates.</td>
      </tr>
    </table>
